                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9722</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-07T23:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 7, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received August 8, 9.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4702. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1"
                        >McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 327. Have submitted subject your No. 223, August 1, to Inter-Allied Black
                    Listing Committee, Paris. French, realizing the political importance, assented
                    to the inclusion of a Japanese delegate on the Paris, London, and Washington
                    committee, but believe Japan should agree (1) to make her regulations governing
                    commerce with the enemy in accord with those of the other Associated
                    Governments, and (2) to adopt the enemy trading lists of the Associated
                    Governments, in so far as possible. British and Italian delegates, Paris
                    committee, are submitting question to their respective governments with
                    favorable recommendation. We will advise you, as soon as we hear from them.
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
